This paper discusses performance metrics for classification models and explores different threshold choice methods. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, but the most likely ones are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with evaluating and improving classification models. The paper also mentions the use of ROC curves, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and the importance of calibration, which is relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and statistics (cs.ST).
